(nL2TLBWays, power_pad).explanation: Increasing the number of ways in L2 TLB requires additional hardware structures and interconnects that directly contribute to pad power consumption for signal routing;

(nL2TLBWays, nICacheTLBWays).explanation: These are independent design parameters for different cache structures (L2 TLB vs instruction cache TLB) that can be configured separately without direct causal relationship;

(nL2TLBWays, power_switching).explanation: More ways in L2 TLB increase the switching activity during address translation operations, directly causing higher dynamic power consumption;
